{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"P0 release-process remediation evaluation (operator-confirmed: NO CHANGES NEEDED).\n\nConcern: 'Releases are insufficiently bound to reviewed and tested source' (v* tag publishes, build-only dependency, mutable action tags, unpinned+unverified mcp-publisher run under OIDC).\n\nThis epic's three release stories remediate the P0 comprehensively (21dd/36c7 are unrelated store/config stories):\n- Tagged SHA must be a tested, submitted Gerrit main revision -> fd84 (F1): workflow_dispatch-from-main (reviewed by construction) + git merge-base --is-ancestor ancestry check. COVERED.\n- Validate vX.Y.Z vs pyproject.toml + server.json -> fd84 (F1): pre-build version-lockstep step asserts version_input == project.version == server.json.version == each packages[].version. COVERED.\n- Pin every action to a full SHA -> 08a8 (F4): full-SHA uses:, enforced by real zizmor under make lint. COVERED.\n- Pin mcp-publisher + verify checksum/signature -> 08a8 (F4): exact-version pin + sha256sum -c + download->verify->execute split into unprivileged mcp_verify / OIDC-privileged mcp_registry (OIDC never co-resident with an unverified binary) + verify_mcp_publisher_pin.py confirms embedded hash matches the URL. COVERED (beyond the literal ask).\n- Build once, preserve provenance, promote exact artifact -> 6168 (F3): build-once -> test exact wheel/sdist in clean jobs -> hash-gated publish (no rebuild) + fixes the Hatchling hook's COMMIT=None wheel-from-sdist defect. COVERED.\n- Keep Trusted Publishing + minimal permissions + PEP 740 -> preserved.\n\nDELIBERATE DIVERGENCE (accepted, no change): 'Protect release tags / restrict tag creation to the release identity' is NOT done as written. fd84 instead REMOVES the tag->publish path entirely (publication only via dispatch-from-main gated on the re-keyed required-reviewers pypi environment; a hand-pushed v* tag cannot reach that environment and cannot publish; the tag is a record-only output created after a successful publish). main.tf's no-tag-lock stance stays (no viable GitHub tag-bypass actor in this mirror topology; codified by test_mirror_lock_terraform). The P0's security INTENT (a rogue tag cannot drive an unreviewed publish) is fully met by eliminating the surface rather than gating it. Operator confirmed this design is acceptable; no additional tag-protection layer will be added in this epic.\n\nOperator-attested dependencies remain for fd84 (F1): configure the live pypi environment (required reviewers + main-only branch policy) and the staging-fork TestPyPI E2E; fd84 adds a release-time preflight that queries the environment via REST and fails the release closed if that protection is missing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784140450524284001,"uuid":"8497d547-f730-4c94-9f9b-ae5d3303a61a"}